THE TOUR CHAMPIONSHIP PRESENTED BY COCA-COLA
September 16, 2007
K.J. Choi
START_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT
 
 
  
 
  
  
   
  Q.  You're still going to make a lot of money for your foundation.   
 K.J. CHOI:  I continue to donate to the foundation to help -- just do a lot of charity work like I've done always.   
  
  Q.  Was it fun being in the mix?   
 K.J. CHOI:  As a player you've got to feel honored to be in that position to have a chance to win the Cup.  You know, it was a motivating factor.   
  
  Q.  Were the Playoffs what you hoped they would be in terms of excitement?  Did you enjoy the four-week Playoffs?   
 K.J. CHOI:  Yeah, I felt very good.  I felt like through the stretch of four tournaments, you know, I was able to elevate my game another notch, and I think just overall it helped me to become a better player.   
   
  End of FastScripts   

END_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT